cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a method for static type analysis of object-oriented languages based on logic programming. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses coinductive logic programming to deal with infinite terms and proofs produced by recursive types and methods. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a method for type-checking and inference in object-oriented languages, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses logic programming to infer precise type information, which is relevant to artificial intelligence. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper deals with the semantics of logic programs and their transformation, which is relevant to formal languages and automata theory.
